        <div class="project-card-large">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">OOP Study Planner System</h5>

            <p class="card-text">
              Developed a Python console application simulating a real-world study planner for students.<br>
              Leveraged object-oriented programming (OOP) principles including encapsulation, class design, and object collaboration.<br>
              Demonstrated initiative to learn advanced OOP concepts beyond the academic syllabus.<br>
            </p>

            <strong>Key Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Add subjects and tasks with deadlines.</li>
                <li>Mark tasks complete, detect overdue work.</li>
                <li>Schedule, update, and cancel study sessions.</li>
                <li>Generate reminders and prioritize tasks.</li>
                <li>Produce simple schedules for all tasks.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="card-text">
              <strong>Tech Stack: </strong><br>
              Language: Python 3.x <br>
              Paradigm: Object-Oriented Programming<br>
              Core Concepts: Encapsulation, Object Collaboration, Class Design, Utility Methods<br>
              Libraries Used: datetime (for managing deadlines and reminders) and Standard Python Built-Ins<br>
            </p>

            <div class="text-center my-3">
              <a href="https://github.com/24020804-MargaretPabustan/Smart-Study-Planner-OOP" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary" style="background-color:#0d6efd; border-color:#0d6efd; border-radius:8px; font-weight:600;">
                View on GitHub
              </a>
            </div>

            <!-- TASK CLASS -->
            <h4 class="card-subtitle text-center mb-3" style="color: #0d6efd;">Task Class</h4>
            <div class="row g-4 justify-content-center">
              <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
                <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm bg-white">
                  <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <img src="/images/task class and attributes.png" alt="Task Class Attributes" 
                        class="img-fluid clickable-image mb-2"
                        style="height:200px; object-fit:contain;"
                        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                        data-image-src="/images/task class and attributes.png"
                        data-image-alt="Task Class Attributes">
                    <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary image-view-button"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                            data-image-src="/images/task class and attributes.png"
                            data-image-alt="Task Class Attributes">
                      View Fullscreen
                    </button>
                    <p class="mt-2"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
                       Displays private Task attributes (title, description, deadline, status), demonstrating <strong>encapsulation</strong> by restricting direct access and protecting data integrity.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
                <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm bg-white">
                  <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <img src="/images/task getter and setter.png" alt="Task Getters & Setters" 
                        class="img-fluid clickable-image mb-2"
                        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                        data-image-src="/images/task getter and setter.png"
                        data-image-alt="Task Getters & Setters">
                    <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary image-view-button"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                            data-image-src="/images/task getter and setter.png"
                            data-image-alt="Task Getters & Setters">
                      View Fullscreen
                    </button>
                    <p class="mt-2"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
                      These are methods that provide controlled access to the private Task attributes. Getters allow reading of attribute values, while setters allow updating them safely with validation, ensuring data integrity.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
                <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm bg-white">
                  <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <img src="/images/task utility methods.png" alt="Task Utility Methods" 
                        class="img-fluid clickable-image mb-2"
                        data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                        data-image-src="/images/task utility methods.png"
                        data-image-alt="Task Utility Methods">
                    <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary image-view-button"
                            data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#imageModal"
                            data-image-src="/images/task utility methods.png"
                            data-image-alt="Task Utility Methods">
                      View Fullscreen
                    </button>
                    <p class="mt-2"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
                      Includes additional functionality such as:<br>
                      <ol>
                        <li>markComplete(): Marks tasks as completed</li> 
                        <li>isOverdue(): Checks whether the student has missed any deadlines</li>
                        <li>displayTask(): Displays task information in a formatted and neat way</li>
                      </ol>
                      These methods make task management efficient for students.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- STUDYSESSION CLASS -->
            <h4 class="card-subtitle text-center mt-4 mb-3" style="color: #0d6efd;">StudySession Class</h4>
            <div class="row g-4 justify-content-center">
              <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
                <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm bg-white">
